jsymbolic2.commandline

Enum CommandLineSwitchEnum

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<CommandLineSwitchEnum>
      • jsymbolic2.commandline.CommandLineSwitchEnum
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<CommandLineSwitchEnum>

    public enum CommandLineSwitchEnum
extends java.lang.Enum<CommandLineSwitchEnum>
    An enumerator for parsing command line arguments and directing execution appropriately. A given enum of the CommandLineSwitchEnum type corresponds to a different type of processing specified at the command line. More particularly, a CommandLineSwitchEnum is initiated by the first command line argument specified at the command line. The switch_string field of a CommandLineSwitchEnum identifies the first command line argument that initiated it, and the switch_actions field identifies the kind of processing that will correspondingly be carried out (via the runProcessing method of the particular SwitchCommandEnum that is pointed to by that field).
    Author:
    Tristano Tenaglia and Cory McKay

      A command line switch for running command line processing using data parsed from a specified configuration file.
      CONSISTENCY_CHECK
      A command line switch for checking if certain musical characteristics are consistent both across a set of MIDI or MEI files, and internally within each file.

      A command line switch for saving extracted feature values in a CSV file.
      GUI
      To run the GUI under default settings.
      HELP
      A command line switch for printing out valid command line usage instructions.
      MIDI_DUMP
      A command line switch for printing out reports on the contents of a MIDI (or converted) MEI files.
      NOSWITCH
      To run via the command line with no switches and only input and output file paths specified.
      VALIDATE_CONFIGURATION_ALL
      A command line switch for checking if the specified configuration file is valid with all data specified, including both input and output save paths.
      VALIDATE_CONFIGURATION_FEATURE_OPTION
      A command line switch for checking if the specified configuration file is valid with all data specified, excluding input and output save paths.
      WINDOW
      A command line switch for running windowed extraction.
